# 6. 意外な一面

Luka: Ichika, you seem a bit down. Is everything all right?
Ichika: Huh? Oh, sorry. I just can't seem to focus.
Luka: It's all right. Remember, you can talk to me if anything is ever bothering you.
Saki: What do you think Ichi and Luka are talking about?
Shiho: I was hoping to play through the set once as a group, but they look like they're going to be a while.
Shiho: I'm going to go practice out in the hall until they're done.
Saki: Huh? Oh, okay.
Miku: In that case, how about the two of us practice? Should we take it from the top?
Saki: .....
Miku: Saki, is everything all right?
Saki: O-Oh, sorry Miku! I was spacing out there for a minute.
Saki: .....
Ichika: I...
Saki: Ichi...
Miku: Did you and Ichika have an argument?
Saki: N-No, it's nothing like that! It's just...
Miku: Hm?
Saki: It's my fault she feels so bad...
Miku: What do you mean?
Miku: So you spoke with Honami?
Saki: Yeah. I told her I would stop bothering her about spending time together and asking her to join the band.
Miku: I see...
Saki: I'm sorry, Miku. After everything I said about never giving up, you're probably disappointed in me...
Miku: Of course not. I think what you did was really cool.
Saki: Huh?
Miku: You clearly want to spend time with Honami, but after giving it careful thought, you decided to do what was least likely to cause her pain. Isn't that right?
Miku: Even though that decision is clearly hard on you.
Miku: That's why it's so cool. I don't think there's anything wrong with your decision, Saki.
Saki: Miku...
Luka: Sorry for the wait, everyone. What do you say we run through everything together?
Saki: Wha?! Oh, sure!
Ichika: Saki, are you all right?
Shiho: You're not feeling unwell again, are you?
Saki: N-No, I'm fine! I was just so focused on my talk with Miku that you startled me, is all.
Luka: Oh, I see. Sorry about that.
Saki: No, it's all right! I was just getting some really great advice from Miku.
Miku: Well, I have been practicing giving advice like a proper senpai since before you all first arrived, you know.
Ichika: What? You have?
Luka: Yes, she's been thinking hard about different ways she might become a more dependable senpai to everyone.
Luka: Like how to sound more grown up. Isn't that right, Miku?
Saki: Really?! Miku did that?!
Miku: A bit, yeah.
Shiho: Wasn't expecting that...
Ichika: You seem so cool and collected. I never expected you to have such a cute side to you.
Miku: C-Cute? That makes it kind of embarrassing...
Saki: Hahaha! We got to see an unexpected side of Miku♪
Shiho: An unexpected side...
Shiho: On first glance, Saki looks like your typical fashion freak, but she's actually pretty normal. I guess you really can't judge a book by its cover.
Saki: H-Hey! You don't have to say it like that!
Ichika: C-Calm down, you two.
Miku: Hehe. I'm glad to see everyone's cheered up a bit.
Luka: I agree.
Miku: Still, what if Honami ends up never coming back?
Luka: We'll just have to believe. I'm sure everything will work out. She'll rediscover her feelings before you know it.
Miku: Yeah, you're right!
